# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat: A new feature
# * fix: A bug fix
# * docs: Documentation only changes
# * style: Code style changes (formatting, missing semicolons, etc)
# * refactor: Code refactoring (neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature)
# * perf: Performance improvements
# * test: Adding or updating tests
# * build: Changes to build system or dependencies
# * ci: CI/CD configuration changes
# * chore: Other changes that don't modify src or test files
# * revert: Revert a previous commit
#
# Scope examples: auth, api, frontend, backend, cli, database, docker, docs, config, tests
#
# Subject line should:
# * Use imperative mood ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
# * Be 50 characters or less
# * Not end with a period
#
# Body should explain what and why vs. how
# Use the body to explain what and why you have done something.
# Wrap it to about 72 characters or so.
#
# Footer should contain any information about Breaking Changes
# and is also the place to reference GitHub issues that this commit closes.
